```{r, message=F}
library(scater)
options(stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
library(here)
```

```{r echo=FALSE,message = FALSE,warning=FALSE,eval=F}
here()
reads <-read.table('legion/temp2', sep = '\t', row.names = 1, header = T, stringsAsFactors = F)
anno<-read.table('legion/sample_names', sep = '\t', header = T)
# names(anno)<-c("sample_name","type")
anno$expt<-as.factor(anno$expt)
anno$gate<-as.factor(anno$gate)
anno$dev_stage<-as.factor(anno$dev_stage)
# make names R compatible
anno$sample_id<-gsub("-","_",anno$sample_id)
reads <- SingleCellExperiment(
     assays = list(counts = as.matrix(reads)),
     colData = anno
)
colnames(reads)<-anno$sample_id
keep_feature <- rowSums(counts(reads) > 0) > 0
reads <- reads[keep_feature, ]
# remove known zeros
reads <- reads[,-grep("zero", reads$sample_id)]
isSpike(reads, "ERCC") <- grepl("^ERCC-", rownames(reads))
#
isSpike(reads, "MT") <- rownames(reads) %in%
    c("ENSG00000198899", "ENSG00000198727", "ENSG00000198888",
    "ENSG00000198886", "ENSG00000212907", "ENSG00000198786",
    "ENSG00000198695", "ENSG00000198712", "ENSG00000198804",
    "ENSG00000198763", "ENSG00000228253", "ENSG00000198938",
    "ENSG00000198840")
#
reads <- calculateQCMetrics(
    reads,
    feature_controls = list(
        ERCC = isSpike(reads, "ERCC"),
        MT = isSpike(reads, "MT")
    )
 )
saveRDS(reads , "reads.RDS")
```

```{r echo=FALSE,message=FALSE,warning=FALSE}
       aes(x = reads$total_features, y = reads$pct_counts_MT, 
           color = reads$dev_stage,shape = reads$expt)) + 
      geom_point(size=2) + 
      geom_line(y=10, colour = "red") +
      scale_colour_discrete(name="developmental\nStage",
                            breaks=c("cord_blood", "CS15", "CS16","CS20","FL8w"),
                            labels=c("cord blood","CS15","CS16","CS20","FL8W")) + 
      scale_shape_discrete(name="experiment") + 
      theme_classic() + 
      xlab("total features") + ylab("percent count mitochondrial") + 
      ggtitle("Mitochondrial vs features")
```

```{r}
reads$use <- (
    # sufficient features (genes)
    filter_by_expr_features &
    # sufficient molecules counted
    filter_by_total_counts &
    # sufficient endogenous RNA
    filter_by_ERCC &
    # remove cells with unusual number of reads in MT genes
    filter_by_MT
)
```

```{r echo=FALSE}
library(limma)
auto <- colnames(reads)[reads$outlier]
man <- colnames(reads)[!reads$use]
venn.diag <- vennCounts(
    cbind(colnames(reads) %in% auto,
    colnames(reads) %in% man)
)
vennDiagram(
    venn.diag,
    names = c("Automatic", "Manual"),
    circle.col = c("blue", "green")
)
```

Applying filters
=============================================

```{r echo=FALSE}

filter_genes <- apply(
    counts(reads[, colData(reads)$use]), 
    1, 
    function(x) length(x[x > 1]) >= 2
)
rowData(reads)$use <- filter_genes

knitr::kable(table(filter_genes))

assay(reads, "logcounts_raw") <- log2(counts(reads) + 1)
reducedDim(reads) <- NULL

saveRDS(reads, file = "filtered_reads.rds")

```


###PCA pre-filtration

```{r}

#library(scater)
options(stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
reads.qc <- reads[rowData(reads)$use, colData(reads)$use]
endog_genes <- !rowData(reads.qc)$is_feature_control

plotPCA(
    reads[endog_genes, ],
    exprs_values = "logcounts_raw",
    size_by = "total_features",
    colour = "dev_stage",
    shape = "gate"
    )
```

###PCA filtered samples and genes

```{r}

plotPCA(
    reads.qc[endog_genes, ],
    exprs_values = "logcounts_raw",
    size_by = "total_features",
    colour = "dev_stage",
    shape = "gate"
)

```

###Identifying explanatory variables


```{r}

plotQC(
    reads.qc[endog_genes, ],
    type = "expl",
    exprs_values = "logcounts_raw",
    variables = c(
        "total_features",
        "total_counts",
        "expt",
        "pct_counts_ERCC",
        "pct_counts_MT"
    )
)
```
